William V. Velez OBITUARY

William V. Velez HAMILTON – William V. Velez, 80, of Hamilton, N.J., passed away on Saturday, May 16, 2015, at home with his loving family by his side. Born in Utuado, Puerto Rico, he was a long time Trenton/Hamilton area resident. William was an entrepreneur and owned many delicatessens in the Trenton area. He was an avid fan of horse racing, boxing and baseball. William was a long time member of the Puerto Rican Community Association in Trenton. Predeceased by his parents, Saturnino Medina and Isabel Velez Feliciano; his daughters, Anita Brennan and Yolanda Velez; his brothers, Ramon Soto Velez and Antonio Soto Velez; his sister, Maria Molina; he is survived by his sons, William Velez and his fiancée, Kymberli Harjes of Hopewell, Richard and Sherry Velez of Ewing and Tony and Colleen Velez of Ewing; his grandchildren, Samantha Brennan and her fiancé, Michael Hall and Ricky, Kristina, Cameron, Lillian and Norah Velez; his nephews, Edwin, Moises, Alberto, Nelson, Fundador, Aristides Molina and a niece, Yolanda Molina; his companion, Naty Gonzalez ; Kymberli Harjes’ children, Luke and Kaempfer, and his beloved dog, Molly. Funeral services will be held on Friday, May 22, 2015, at 11:30 a.m. at the Saul Colonial Home, 3795 Nottingham Way, Hamilton Square, NJ. Interment will follow at St. Mary’s Cemetery, Hamilton. Family and friends may call on Thursday, May 21, 2015, from 6:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. at the Saul Colonial Home. In lieu of flowers, contributions may be made in William’s memory to the American Liver Foundation, 39 Broadway, Suite 2700, New York, NY 10006, The Brain Aneurysm Foundation, 269 Hanover St., #3, Hanover, MA 02339 or CARES Foundation, 2414 Morris Ave., Suite 110, Union, NJ 07083. www.saulfuneralhomes.com
